---
import CodeBlock from './CodeBlock.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 space-y-32 container mx-auto px-4">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl reveal">
        <h1 class="text-6xl md:text-8xl font-black text-white impact mb-8 leading-none">
            AI AGENT <br>
            <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-cyber-cyan to-cyber-pink">SANDBOXING</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-400 font-mono tracking-tight leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-cyber-cyan pl-6">
            A guide to orchestrating high-velocity AI agents using the Bare Hub infrastructure. 
            Maximize agent autonomy while protecting your primary development environment.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 01. Why Sandbox? -->
    <div class="reveal space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyber-cyan font-black text-4xl impact">01</span>
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-white impact tracking-widest uppercase">Why Sandbox?</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-slate-400 text-sm">
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold impact uppercase">No Collisions</h4>
                <p>AI agents often make massive, sweeping changes. In a worktree, these changes are isolated. Your main `git status` remains clean.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold impact uppercase">Parallelism</h4>
                <p>Run three different agents on three different bugs simultaneously. Each has its own physical directory and process space.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/50 border border-slate-800 rounded-xl">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold impact uppercase">Safe Context</h4>
                <p>Agents won't see your uncommitted experiments or sensitive local files that aren't part of the branch history.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 02. Deployment Protocol -->
    <div class="reveal space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyber-pink font-black text-4xl impact">02</span>
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-white impact tracking-widest uppercase">Deployment Protocol</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-16">
            <!-- Step 1 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-cyber-pink/20 flex items-center justify-center text-cyber-pink font-bold">1</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white impact">Initialize the Sandbox</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Create a dedicated worktree for the specific ticket or task. This ensures the agent has a clean, branch-specific slate.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`# Create a new worktree at ../agent-fix for a specific feature
git worktree add ../agent-fix -b ai/fix-issue-123
cd ../agent-fix`} label="SANDBOX // INIT" />
            </div>

            <!-- Step 2 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-cyber-pink/20 flex items-center justify-center text-cyber-pink font-bold">2</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white impact">Engage the Agent</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Launch your AI tool within the sandbox directory. The agent now has exclusive access to this isolated environment.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`# For Claude Code
claude "Fix the layout bug in Header.astro"

# For Gemini CLI
gemini-cli "Refactor the authentication middleware"`} label="SANDBOX // ENGAGE" />
            </div>

            <!-- Step 3 -->
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                    <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded bg-cyber-pink/20 flex items-center justify-center text-cyber-pink font-bold">3</div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white impact">Review & Merge</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl">Once the agent finishes, review the changes in the sandbox. If satisfied, commit and push, or merge into your primary branch.</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`git add .
git commit -m "ai: fix layout bug"
git push origin ai/fix-issue-123

# Clean up the muscle
cd ..
git worktree remove agent-fix`} label="SANDBOX // CLEANUP" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 03. Multi-Agent Orchestration -->
    <div class="reveal space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-cyber-green font-black text-4xl impact">03</span>
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-white impact tracking-widest uppercase">Multi-Agent Orchestration</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-800/20 p-10 rounded-3xl border border-slate-700">
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
                The Bare Hub truly shines when managing multiple agents. Use a naming convention for your sandbox directories to maintain clarity.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="p-6 bg-black/40 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
                    <h4 class="text-cyber-green font-bold impact mb-3">CONCURRENT AUDIT</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">Run a security audit agent and a performance audit agent at the same time.</p>
                    <ul class="text-[0.65rem] font-mono text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                        <li>üìÅ audits/security</li>
                        <li>üìÅ audits/performance</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="p-6 bg-black/40 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
                    <h4 class="text-cyber-green font-bold impact mb-3">TICKET PIPELINE</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4">Assign separate tickets to separate agent instances.</p>
                    <ul class="text-[0.65rem] font-mono text-slate-400 space-y-1">
                        <li>üìÅ tasks/fix-nav</li>
                        <li>üìÅ tasks/update-docs</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 04. Expert Tips -->
    <div class="reveal space-y-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-white font-black text-4xl impact">04</span>
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-black text-white impact tracking-widest uppercase">Expert Tips</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="border-l-2 border-cyber-cyan pl-6 py-2">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Automate Node Installs</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Use a `post-checkout` Git hook in your `.bare` engine to automatically run `pnpm install` when a new worktree is created.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-2 border-cyber-pink pl-6 py-2">
                <h4 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Shared Build Cache</h4>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Configure your build tools (Turborepo, Nx) to use a global cache so agents don't waste time rebuilding components you've already compiled.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
